physical_appearance: This is a photograph of the Shwedagon Pagoda in Rangoon, Burma. The photograph features a cluster of pagodas of varying heights. On the bottom-right of the photograph, there is a statue of a chinthe. On the bottom-left, there is a statue of another chinthe, with a human head. There are three men standing in between the two statues. The title is written at the bottom, below the photograph.
title_text: Photograph album of views and portraits in the Punjab, Cashmere, Ceylon, Burma, Penang, Singapore, and Java Base of Shwedagon Pagoda, Rangoon
